===Verb===
{{en-verb|judg|ing}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To sit in [[judgment]] on; to [[pass]] [[sentence]] on.
#: ''A higher power will '''judge''' you after you are dead.''
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To sit in judgment, to act as judge.
#: ''Justices in this country '''judge''' without appeal.''
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[form]] an [[opinion]] on.
#: ''I '''judge''' a man’s character by the cut of his suit.''
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To [[arbitrate]]; to pass [[opinion]] on something, especially to [[settle]] a [[dispute]] etc.
#: ''We cannot both be right: you must '''judge''' between us.''
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To have as an opinion; to [[consider]], [[suppose]].
#: ''I '''judge''' it safe to leave the house once again.''
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To form an opinion; to [[infer]].
#: ''I '''judge''' from the sky that it might rain later.''
#* '''1884''': {{w|Mark Twain}}, {{w|The Adventures of Huckleberry Finn}}, Chapter VIII
#*: THE sun was up so high when I waked that I '''judged''' it was after eight o'clock.
# {{context|transitive|intransitive|lang=en}} To [[criticize]] or [[label]] another person or thing.
